---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import NewsletterCTA from '../components/NewsletterCTA.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy & How We Review"
  description={`How ${SITE.name} chooses, plays, scores and updates the games we cover — and the standards behind every recommendation.`}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 sm:px-6">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Editorial Policy' }]} />
    <article class="prose prose-lg mt-6 max-w-none">
      <h1>Editorial Policy &amp; How We Review</h1>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} exists to help you find cozy games worth your time and money. To be useful, our
        advice has to be trustworthy — so here is exactly how we choose what to cover, how we play
        and score games, how we stay current, and how the site is funded. If we ever fall short of
        these standards, please <a href="/contact">tell us</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Independence comes first</h2>
      <p>
        Our recommendations are never for sale. No developer, publisher or store can pay for a
        positive review, a higher score, or a place on one of our lists. We don't accept payment in
        exchange for coverage, and a free review copy of a game never obligates us to be kind to it.
        When we say a game is worth your money, it's because we believe it.
      </p>

      <h2>How we choose what to cover</h2>
      <p>
        We focus on the cozy and simulation corner of gaming — farming sims, life sims, gentle
        building and management games, and relaxing adventures. We prioritise games that genuinely
        fit that brief: low-stress, welcoming, and rewarding to unwind with. Lists are curated by
        hand, not generated automatically, and we only include a game when we can say something
        useful about <em>why</em> it earns its place.
      </p>

      <h2>How we play and test</h2>
      <p>
        We base our reviews and recommendations on hands-on time with the games — playing them as a
        real player would, across the platforms most people will use. For bigger sims that means
        many hours; for shorter games it often means seeing them through to the end. Where a game is
        still evolving (early access or live-service titles), we say so, and we tell you what state
        it's in at the time of writing.
      </p>

      <h2>How our scores work</h2>
      <p>Reviews carry a score out of 5. Here's roughly what each level means:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>4.5–5</strong> — Exceptional. A standout we'd recommend to almost anyone in the mood for it.</li>
        <li><strong>4–4.4</strong> — Great. Well worth your time, with only minor caveats.</li>
        <li><strong>3–3.9</strong> — Good, but with real trade-offs. Worth it for the right player.</li>
        <li><strong>Below 3</strong> — Flawed enough that we'd suggest waiting, or looking elsewhere first.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Every review spells out the trade-offs in plain language — the pros, the cons, and exactly
        who we think will (and won't) enjoy it — so the score is never the whole story.
      </p>

      <h2>Keeping content current</h2>
      <p>
        Cozy games change: prices move, updates land, and free games get bigger. We revisit and
        update our most useful articles, and when an article has been meaningfully revised we show an
        "Updated" date on it. Live prices in our "where to buy" panels refresh automatically. If you
        spot something out of date or incorrect, <a href="/contact">let us know</a> and we'll fix it.
      </p>

      <h2>How the site is funded</h2>
      <p>
        Some links on {SITE.name} are affiliate links: if you buy through them, we may earn a small
        commission at no extra cost to you. That support helps keep the site running and free to
        read, but it never influences our opinions, scores, or which games we recommend. You can read
        the full <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a> any time.
      </p>

      <h2>Corrections &amp; feedback</h2>
      <p>
        We're a small, independent site and we get things wrong sometimes. If you find a factual
        error, a broken link, or a game we should be covering, please <a href="/contact">get in
        touch</a>. We read every message and update accordingly.
      </p>
    </article>

    <NewsletterCTA class="mt-12" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
